   THURMAN-MISANTHROPE (New York) _ Actress Uma Thurman, another in
a line of movie stars who have been trying the stage lately, has
chosen one of theater's most difficult parts: the lead female role
in an update of Moliere's ``Misanthrope,'' which must be recited
almost entirely in rhymed couplets. By Dinitia Smith.
