<P>
   OLY-SCANDAL-UTAH (Salt Lake City) _ K. McCoy Livingston, a
bookish flower seller here who reveres history and loves to quote
the English philosopher John Locke on the burdens of liberty,
bumped up against the Olympics a few years back. It nearly broke
him. One of his shops, The Flower Patch, had encountered what many
people here call the Web _ a seamless, often invisible network of
economic and personal relationships among Utah's leaders in
business and politics that quietly influences, if it doesn't quite
control, much of the state's economy and civic life. By Kirk
Johnson.
