retailing gimmick _ use a check or credit card at a store equipped
with ``True ID'' and the clerk could call up a tiny, computerized
photo to verify the identity of the purchaser. But in the past two
weeks, residents in South Carolina, Florida and Colorado were
infuriated to learn this new system is being built on driver's
license photos and related personal information purchased from the
states' motor vehicle bureaus. By KIM COBB.
