   LOOK ON THE WEB: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are available
for purchase in paginated form: www.nytsyn.com/pageexpress.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH _ PERSONAL TECHNOLOGY _ You've heard about the
lightning-fast speed in which cable modems operate and you're tired
of the hassles brought by dial-up service to the Net such as
frequent busy signals, that annoying sound a modem makes dialing in
to the server and broken connections. But is it everything you've
wanted? Here's the lowdown on cable modems. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET CONS _ The more the Internet grows and the more new
users it attracts, the greater the opportunities for those who
wouldn't mind conning newbies out of their money. (Gallaga, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   TECH BRIEFS _ Powered by a little computer that looks like an
iridescent gumdrop, Apple Computer continues to grow stronger.
(Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ Life on the Web mirrors life. As the Web has
become a tool, instead of just an amusement , the ability to search
for needed information has become more important. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: This is the CoxNet PTECH page for the current week. This
layout is now available.)
</P>
<P>
   TECH-CENTERPIECE-BLACKSOFTWARE _ Weekly centerpiece on personal
technology, from products to trends to advancements. This week:
Microsoft Encarta Africana software, featuring information about
African-American history, important figures and culture. (Poole,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTO. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TECH-CENTERPIECE-SIDE _ A list of Web sites that are also useful
when searching for information about African-Americans. (Poole,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   DDN-COX-USERGROUPS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ User groups are collections
of people who get together to compare notes, share experiences and
improve their skills on their favorite type of computer. (Cummings,
Dayton Daily News) 31. WITH ILLUSTRATION on Cox Server. MOVED
SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   DDN-COX-HDTV _ DAYTON, Ohio _ High-definition television sets
are coming down in size and price. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) 8.
MOVED SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY_ Popular column about personal computing written for
the average user. This week: My thoughts on Y2K. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TECHTOOLS _ Software reviews. This week: Making the transition
to Windows 98. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETWATCH _ This column will not run this week. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
