week: Making new PCs faster and the CD game ``Populous.'' (Haddad,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MAC-REPORT _ This column will not run this week. (Haddad,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TECH-REPORT _ Tech briefs on new products and developments. This
week: Linking to legislative offices and petition sites, 3-D for
camcorders and a Compaq-eBay deal. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   POWERUSER-COLUMN _ A regular series of columns for advanced
computer users. This week: enhancing gaming experiences. (Yandel,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERQ&AMP;A _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumer Q&AMP;A. This week: Would
Clinton keep his retirement benefits if convicted by the Senate,
and other consumer questions. (Greig, Austin American-Statesman)
(l, a) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   TVSURFER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ ``Frontline'' airs ``The Execution''
about Texas valedictorian who became a murderer. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)ETA: 6 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   REM _ ATHENS, Ga. _ Great secrecy surrounds a press conference
R.E.M. is holding in Athens at 1 p.m. Monday. But word on the
street is that the band is going to announce it plans to play
several Atlanta dates at Chastain Park Amphitheatre, and might even
launch an American tour. We'll attend the press conference, and
report on what R.E.M. is up to. (Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NEWSSTAND _ Periodicals on the newsstands this week. (O'Briant,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
