<HEADLINE>
`ANTZ' IS FOR EVERYONE; `WONDERLAND' IS A BALL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Antz'' _ One of the best animated films released
last year. Woody Allen, spoofing his angst-ridden persona, is
terrific as the psychiatric patient ant bemoaning his troubles
while lying on a leaf. Enough sophistication for adults while still
appealing to children.
</P>
<P>
   ``Next Stop Wonderland'' _ Boston-area fans will enjoy the
settings for this well-received independent film. The notion of
romantic timing is wonderfully explored, and the performances are
first-rate. The story sags a bit, but the end result is satisfying.
</P>
<P>
   ``Rounders'' _ Edward Norton and Matt Damon head a smart cast in
director John Dahl's provocative exploration of high-stakes poker.
The carefully detailed character study keeps a dead-eye on the
steely professionalism of a group of card players. A film as tough
and hard-headed as Amarillo Slim.
</P>
<P>
   ``Legionnaire'' _ This big-budget Claude Van Damme feature
sacrifices action for character and plot development. No surprise
there. This foreign-legion, direct-to-video release gets stuck in
the sand. Rent ``Lawrence of Arabia'' or ``Gunga Din'' instead.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Feb. 16: ``Snake Eyes,'' ``Beyond Silence,''
``First Love, Last Rites,'' ``The Governess,'' ``This Is the Sea,''
``Without Limits.'' Feb. 23: ``Ronin,'' ``Carnival of Souls,''
``The Manchurian Candidate,'' ``Pecker.'' March 2: ``Dark City,''
``Tom and Jerry: The Movie,'' ``A Winter Tan,'' ``The Island of Dr.
Moreau.'' March 9: ``What Dreams May Come,'' ``Dead Man on
Campus,'' ``Black Dog,'' ``Slam,'' ``Somebody Is Waiting.'' March
16: ``The Waterboy,'' ``Bulworth,'' ``No Laughing Matter,''
``Living Out Loud,'' ``One True Thing,'' ``Polish Wedding,'' ``Paul
Monette: The Brink of Summer's End,'' ``The Wonderful Ice Cream
Suit,'' ``Who the Hell Is Juliette?'' March 23: ``Pleasantville,''
``Firelight,'' ``Bride of Chucky,'' ``Jerry Springer's
Ringmaster,'' ``From Dusk Till Dawn 2,'' ``Strike!'' March 30:
``The Rugrats Movie,'' ``Mutual Needs.'' April 6: ``The Dentist
2.'' April 27: ``Happiness.''
</P>
