   &UR; KING HUSSEIN &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans a 2-page package of stories on the
funeral of Jordan's King Hussein.
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-FUNERAL (Amman) _ United in loss and grief, a vast array
of presidents, prime ministers and princes gathered here Monday to
join the late King Hussein on his final journey, as his body was
buried in a humble white shroud. The mourners included the
bitterest of foes, most notably the leaders of Syria and Israel, a
tribute in death to a Jordanian monarch who in life, over nearly
half a century's reign, had sought to bridge even the most
rancorous of disputes. By Douglas Jehl.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-SCENE (Amman) _ A view from the streets as Jordanians
watch the king's body pass and wonder what comes next for a kingdom
facing economic hardship and worries about neighboring iraq. By
William A. Orme Jr.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
