stories for Tuesday. If you have questions, please call Chuck Lewis
or Tim Spence at 202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all
sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ House prosecutors and White House
lawyers make final pitches to the Senate in President Clinton's
impeachment trial amid signs that the chief executive may escape
censure by the Senate. Senate Minority Leader Tom Daschle, D-S.D.,
concedes uphill battle to overcome threatened GOP filibuster
against censure resolution. By STEWART M. POWELL, JUDY HOLLAND And
JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The polls indicate the Republicans
may be hurt by the impeachment charade in the year 2000 elections.
But public memory is short. Can the Democrats keep the rumpus alive
by denouncing the GOP as the party of intolerant snoops and the
Republicans neutralize their image by calling the Democrats the
party of immorality? By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
