   PROS
</P>
<P>
   MARTIN-FEDS _ Falcons wide receiver Tony Martin turns himself in
to federal authorities in Miami and is charged with five counts of
money-laundering and conspiracy. Each carries a maximum penalty of
20 years in prison. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BROWNS-ADVANCE _ On the eve of Tuesday's expansion draft,
Cleveland Browns coach Chris Palmer says he looking for a handful
of good players to come out of this draft. Palmer is thinking that
if he can get five decent players, he'll be happy. His message to
the available players: You can prove to the teams that left you
unprotected that you are not washed up. Top players available are
Darrien Gordon, who had two picks in the Super Bowl, and Neil
Smith, both of Denver, top the list of players available. Atlanta's
unprotected players are guard Dave Widell, linebacker Ben Talley,
tight end Ed Smith, running back Harold Green and Chris Bayne, a
defensive back. (Ludwig, Dayton Daily News). 15.
</P>
