<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   NBA
</P>
<P>
   HAWKS _ ATLANTA _ Advance, Hawks at Bulls. On a night when
Chicago should be celebrating an NBA title, the Hawks go in for the
Bulls' home opener playing a decimated team with low expectations.
(Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   BKC-AUBURN _ The Auburn Tigers have had their share of talented
players and teams during its 93 years of basketball, but this
year's team has an opportunity tonight to earn its place in the
school record books. Auburn enters tonight's game against
Mississippi with a 22-1 record, tying the school record for wins in
a season, and can set a new mark with a win over the Rebels.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journa)-Constitution). 12-14.
</P>
