<P>
   CLINTON-HUSSEIN _ AMMAN, Jordan _ During six years of on-again
off-again efforts to end half a century of enmity and bloodshed in
the Middle East, Clinton has known no more steadfast a companion in
the peace process than King Hussein, whose remains were laid to
rest here Monday. Now, with the peace process stalled and lurching
toward a potentially disasterous May 4 deadline for the resolution
of a thorny set of outstanding issues between Palestinians and
Israelis, the White House is contemplating the abscence of a man
National Security adviser Samuel Berger called, ''the transcendent
voice for war and peace in the Middle East over the past several
years.'' (Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   w/ HUSSEIN-FUNERAL _ AMMAN, Jordan _ With one of the largest and
most diverse groups of world leaders in attendance, Jordan's King
Hussein bin Talal was laid to rest on Monday, as the world paid
tribute to a great peacemaker and at the same time wondered about
the stability of this turbulent region. Developing. (Deans, Cox
News Service)
</P>
<P>
   HUSSEIN-JORDAN _ AMMAN, Jordan _ By the thousands they came.
From the lowliest subjects of this tiny desert kingdom to the
members of the most exclusive club on the planet, the former
presidents of the United States, they lined streets and stood in
long lines to pay tribute to the boy monarch who became a keystone
for peace in an oft-troubled land. The color and scene. Developing.
(Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
