<HEADER>
A6593 &Cx1f; ttf-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NYLITE-2NDTAKE-NYT &LR;      02-08 1605
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NYLITE-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
  
 UNDATED: Fiona McKinney.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Penny Kemp and Linda Falk had trekked out to Southern California
for the Rose Bowl. On the drive to Malibu for a pregame party, they
spotted a car with the vanity plate ``OYGRWUP.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Hey, Linda, look! That license plate says, `Oy, Grow up,' Ms.
Kemp exclaimed.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're in California, not New York,'' Ms. Falk retorted. ``It
says, `Oh, why grow up?'''
</P>
<P>
   The worst time in Manhattan is a rainy cold winter day at rush
hour in midtown trying to get home. But last week, because of a bus
driver, I felt like a tourist just enjoying the Big Apple.
</P>
<P>
   The crosstown M42 bus was packed with tired commuters. People
were growing irritated at the slow traffic and being squeezed into
inches of space. The bus driver picked up the microphone to
announce what we thought would be the next stop.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, his announcement went something like this: ``Fifth
Avenue is the next stop. Look out the window. It's the magnificent
Fifth Avenue with everything your heart desires. Go up to see the
one and only Central Park and enjoy Museum Mile with the best
museums in New York and in this world, from the Metropolitan Museum
to MOMA, from ancient Egyptian arts to contemporary paintings. Now
turn to your left and you will find the beautiful New York Public
Library. Farther down is the famous Empire State Building and the
World Trade Center. Now you are here _ Fifth Avenue, Fifth Avenue,
everyone who wants to get off, please use the rear door.''
</P>
<P>
   Thank you, sir.
</P>
<P>
   _ KARLEEN CHIU
</P>
<P>
   Pamela Puckett, in a midtown card store, heard a woman asking
the clerk: ``Don't you have any cheap Valentine's Day cards for
husbands?''
</P>
<P>
   Michael Antonoff was standing inside the door of a pizzeria in
the theater district, awaiting the arrival of his lunch date. A
deliveryman walked in, carrying two bags of Chinese food. The
maitre d'hotel shook her head, suggested that the food must be for
the office upstairs and pointed to the next door.
</P>
<P>
   After the deliveryman insisted that he had the right address,
the maitre d' checked with the kitchen. A minute later, the cook
emerged, took possession of the food and disappeared back into the
kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   Antonoff couldn't help but exclaim, ``It's a bad omen.''
</P>
<P>
   The maitre d'hotel had obviously been briefed. ``No,'' she
replied. ``the chef eats the same food every day and just wanted
something different.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Atlanta Falcons' Eugene Robinson is gonna give back the Bart
Starr Award for high morality in the NFL. He got the award the day
he was arrested for soliciting a prostitute. I thought this was
very nice. He said it wouldn't be right to have something sitting
on his mantelpiece that's big and heavy and his wife could throw at
him.''
</P>
<P>
   ``As I mentioned yesterday, Dan Quayle announced he is running
for President of the United States. And today he said if he can't
be President, he'll settle for a new dirt bike.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A company is coming out with a Bill Clinton cologne. And this
is great cologne, 'cause no matter what you do, you wind up
smelling like a rose. It's the best cologne!'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Gary Coleman's trial is underway. He's accused of punching a
woman who asked him for an autograph. And today the judge ordered
the woman to undergo a psychiatric exam to find out why the hell
she was asking Gary Coleman for his autograph.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Muhammad Ali has been chosen to be on the 75th anniversary
cereal box of Wheaties. And in a related story, Atlanta Falcons'
Eugene Robinson is gonna be on a box of Trix.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not official, but Dennis Rodman may be coming to the L.A.
Lakers. His agent says Dennis prefers L.A. because he wants to
continue living within 10 miles of his wife, Carmen Electra.
They're very close.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to the Star, Soon-Yi has put Woody Allen on Viagra
because they want to start a family. I guess Soon-Yi is anxious to
have a little sister.''
</P>
<P>
   ``At the Los Angeles Zoo, a female chimpanzee gave birth, but
all the male chimps at the zoo have had vasectomies, and today the
zookeeper, Joey Buttafuoco, said he didn't know anything about
it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Michael Jackson is recovering from a broken wrist. You can
pretty much write your own joke there.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Monica Lewinsky testified in the impeachment trial yesterday.
When Lewinsky was asked if there was any obstruction, Monica said,
'Well, the dress did kinda get in the way.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Several senators have said that they want the final vote for
the impeachment trial to be held on Abraham Lincoln's birthday.
Afterwards, a very confused Strom Thurmond said he won't be able to
attend because he's going to Lincoln's birthday party.''
</P>
<P>
   ``People who watched the Super Bowl with President Clinton said
they were impressed with all the sports trivia about football he
knows. For example, the President says Denver is the team with the
most cheerleaders named Tiffany.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In a new interview, Kate Winslet says that whenever she gets
depressed she thinks of her love scene in 'Titanic' with Leonardo
DiCaprio. Meanwhile, Leonardo DiCaprio says that whenever he gets
depressed, he just has sex with a super model.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to a new poll, after watching the impeachment trial,
two-thirds of Americans don't think live witnesses are necessary.
Meanwhile, the other one-third said that after watching the
impeachment trial, they don't think the Senate is necessary.''
</P>
<P>
   ``President Clinton and Hillary were in town last night for a
fundraiser where they charged $10,000 a head. In a related story,
Monica Lewinsky was in town to raise funds and she charged $10,000
a head.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The other day, police in London arrested actor Johnny Depp
because he was swinging a long, thin wooden plank at a group of
photographers. Later, Depp was let go because they realized the
thin wooden plank was just Kate Moss.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Hillary Clinton is very upset because her daughter Chelsea is
featured on the cover of the next issue of 'People.' Hillary's also
upset because her husband Bill is on the cover of the next issue of
'Big Booty.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``In a speech yesterday, Al Gore said that it's time that the
Senate stopped trying to impeach the President. Gore went on to
say, 'But folks, I do appreciate the effort.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Earlier today in California, Tiger Woods and Kevin Costner
teamed up for a charity golf tournament. Apparently everything was
going fine until Kevin Costner got stuck on a water hazard and
spent $200 million.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Last night, thousands of Internet users were very disappointed
because they were unable to log on to Victoria Secret's Web site
and watch the live fashion show. Afterwards, several computer users
said they've had it with the Internet and they're going back to
being rejected by women in person.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday at the impeachment trial, a heckler in the Senate
gallery was arrested after standing up and yelling, 'Take a vote,
let's get it over with.' The weird thing is, it was President
Clinton.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Thanks to an overwhelming vote at the impeachment trial
yesterday, Monica Lewinsky will not be appearing on the floor of
the Senate. After hearing this, President Clinton said, 'What about
the floor of the Oval Office?'''
</P>
<P>
   ``The NBA season starts tonight and you can tell the players are
a little out of shape. In fact, at practice yesterday Latrell
Sprewell got winded halfway through strangling his coach.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A new book came out this week called 'A Complete Guide to
Everything Men Need to Know About Sex,' and this book tells men all
the ways to make sex more satisfying for women. There's also an
edition written telling women what men like, but all it says is
'Say Yes.'''
</P>
