 &QL; 
BARGER-HELL'S ANGELS - Sonny Barger, regarded by police as an
international leader of the Hell's Angels motorcycle group, has
relocated from Oakland to the Phoenix area and has opened a
motorcycle shop in Glendale, Ariz.: Sonny Barger Motors Inc.
Barger, 60, was the founder of the Oakland chapter of Hell's Angels
in 1957 and has often been portrayed in the news media as a
charismatic leader. Police say they are aware he is here, but don't
say much beyond that. ``God bless him,'' said one Phoenix cop. ``We
wish him well in his business, as we would any businessman.'' By
BRENT WHITING. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
