<P>
   JORDAN-NOOR (Amman, Jordan) _ How has Queen Noor balanced
Western womanhood with Arab customs? Her experience at the funeral
is a case in point. By Charles M. Sennott. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-CLINTON (Amman, Jordan) _ King Hussein's death gives
President Clinton a rare opportunity to work on foreign policy. By
Ann Scales. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-TALKS (Paris) _ While a settlement proposal being
circulated among the warring factions in Kosovo is largely a
product of US envoy Christopher Hill, the ability to sell the
settlement and then police it will be primarily a European
challenge. By Kevin Cullen. 800 words.
</P>
