<P>
   SBC-WILLIAMS (Undated) _ Trying to become a national
communications provider, SBC Communications Inc. on Monday said it
would buy up to 10 percent of the Williams Companies Inc.'s
communications unit, which is building a coast-to-coast fiber-optic
network. The deal between SBC, the No. 2 local phone company, and
Williams could be worth as much as $500 million and would be the
first significant investment in a long-distance carrier by one of
the Bell local phone giants. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
