   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ House prosecutors bring their
impeachment case to a close with a final plea that President
Clinton be removed from office, urging senators not to be ``fooled
by the president's excuses.'' The chief White House lawyer counters
that Clinton's behavior, while admittedly reckless, does not ``put
at risk the liberties of the people,'' and accuses lawmakers of
hurting the country by wanting to win too much. By R.W. Apple Jr.
(The story has moved in ``w'' news file.)
