transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SCI-FALSE-DATA-NYT (moved on Friday, Feb. 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Feb. 5,
about falsified data in a Federally sponsored breast cancer study
described the fraud incompletely. Leaders of the study said that
the essence of it was the assertion by a research nurse that three
patients in the study were alive and well when they in fact were
dead.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SIEBERT-MARKETPLACE-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Feb. 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Feb. 3,
about a recent surge in the price of Siebert Financial Corporation
stock, misstated the number of company shares that are publicly
traded. It is 2 million, not 710,000.
